wayfaring stranger anglo american song wayfaring stranger anglo american song facebook twitter email print add to calendar you are invited to join marsha genensky one of the founding members of the internationally renowned vocal quartet anonymous 4 and singers from her winter quarter continuing studies course for an exploration concert of songs from living anglo american musical traditions including classic and broadside ballads gospel songs from the civil war era and beyond and sentimental and tin pan alley songs songs like these formed the rich musical heritage of such artists as the carter family the stanley brothers the everly brothers and many more and are still favorites with oldtime bluegrass newgrass country and folk musicians in the us and beyond this program designed by the class will include original versions of the old songs arrangements of them in more recent styles and new arrangements and compositions please stay and sing a few tunes with us after the performance is over a convivial reception will follow the performance when tuesday march 22 2011 7 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where campbell recital hall braun music center map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor continuing studies contact 725 2650 continuingstudies stanford edu admission free and open to public permalink http events stanford edu events 258 25883 more info last modified march 3 2011
